message.content:
- Present: I'm going to the store.
- Past: I was going to the store.
- Future: I will go to the store.
- Imperative: Go to the store!

The present tense is used to indicate actions that are currently happening. The past tense is used to indicate actions that have already happened. The future tense is used to indicate actions that will happen in the future. The imperative tense is used to give orders or requests..
